      "comment": "MAD MONDAY (11) is unbeaten in three appearances here this campaign. Pushed to the front and kept going to score in the G2 Preux Chevalier 4YO Classic last time. Drops in distance but his record at it is strong. With even luck from the back row and he could continue on his winning way. BETTORS PRIDE (3) has the hoof on the till after placing in his last three starts. Good effort for second and just a neck from the winner in a good line-up last week. A nice draw on the front line could see him break through. HUGOTASTIC NZ (4) enjoys a big class drop after contesting the Nullabor and Fremantle Cup in his last two outings. Was just 1.4m off Magnificent Storm in the Bunbury Cup prior. That is good form for this. IM LIGHTNING BANNER NZ (1) has been coming from wider or second row draws so can be competitive from the inside barrier.",
